# Localman

Offline-first desktop API client (Postman alternative) — Tauri + React + TypeScript.

**Status:** Phases 0–6 & 12–13 complete. Phase 10 (CI/CD & Packaging) in progress. [See roadmap](docs/development-roadmap.md).

## Features

- **Request Builder** — All HTTP methods, auth types (Basic, Bearer, API Key, OAuth 2.0), headers, body
- **Collections & Folders** — Organize requests in nested folders, workspace-scoped
- **Environments** — Variable interpolation (`{{varName}}`, `{{$guid}}`, `{{$timestamp}}`)
- **Code Snippets** — Generate code in 16 languages (cURL, JavaScript, Python, Go, Java, PHP, C#, Ruby, etc.)
- **API Documentation** — Markdown descriptions, HTML/Markdown export, table of contents
- **Cloud Sync** — Firebase OAuth, team workspaces, field-level conflict resolution
- **WebSocket Real-Time** — Live entity updates, presence tracking, auto-reconnect
- **Pre/Post Scripts** — QuickJS sandbox for request/response manipulation
- **History & Analytics** — Auto-logged executions, searchable
- **Offline-First** — Works without internet; syncs when online (LWW + 3-way merge)
- **Auto-Update** — Signed GitHub releases with cross-platform builds (Windows/macOS/Linux)

## Prerequisites

- **Node.js** 20+ and **pnpm**
- **Rust** (required for Tauri): [rustup.rs](https://rustup.rs)
  - Windows: Run `rustup-init.exe`, restart terminal
  - macOS/Linux: `curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh`
  - Verify: `cargo --version`

## Quick Start

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-org/localman.git
cd localman
pnpm install
pnpm tauri dev        # Desktop app with hot reload
```

For frontend-only dev (browser): `pnpm dev`

## Backend Setup (Optional — for Cloud Sync)

```bash
cd backend
cp .env.example .env   # Fill in FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT, DATABASE_URL
npm install
npm run dev            # Hono server on :3000
```

See [Backend Guide](docs/codebase-summary.md#backend-architecture-phase-13--new) for PostgreSQL setup.

## Testing & CI

- **Unit tests** — `pnpm test` (35 tests, Vitest)
- **E2E tests** — `pnpm test:e2e` (Playwright)
- **Lint** — `pnpm lint` (ESLint)
- **Type-check** — `pnpm type-check` (TypeScript)
- **Cross-platform** — See [Testing Checklist](docs/cross-platform-testing.md)
- **CI/CD** — GitHub Actions (lint, test on every push; release builds on tags `v*`)

## Documentation

- [**Codebase Summary**](docs/codebase-summary.md) — Directory structure, 86 components, 11 stores, 50 services
- [**System Architecture**](docs/system-architecture.md) — Data flow, offline-first, WebSocket real-time, 3-way merge
- [**Development Roadmap**](docs/development-roadmap.md) — Phase history, features per phase, known issues
